      "stepTherapy": "No explicit MassHealth-wide statement of 'PA required if 2+ concurrent agents in class,' but many individual non-preferred formulations require documented inadequate response/adverse reaction to one or more preferred NSAIDs (e.g., ketorolac tablets/injection above quantity limits requires a trial of three different NSAIDs; Arthrotec, Duexis, and Vimovo require PA specifically for members under 60).",
      "tier": "No explicit dollar/tier language; MassHealth states 'In general, MassHealth requires a trial of the preferred drug or clinical rationale for prescribing a non-preferred drug,' though this class has no single named preferred agent — most standard oral generic NSAID tablets/capsules (naproxen, ibuprofen, celecoxib, meloxicam tablet, etc.) are simply covered without PA.",
      "verification": "verified",
      "verificationNote": "Read directly from the MassHealth Drug List (MHDL) Table 11: Nonsteroidal Anti-Inflammatory Drugs (pubtheradetail.do?id=11), Original Effective Date 09/2002, Last Revised Date 04/2026. Confirmed the full list of ~55 distinct NSAID drug/formulation entries across acetic acid derivatives, anthranilic acid derivatives, enolic acid derivatives, phenylacetic acid derivatives, propionic acid derivatives, salicylic acid derivative, and COX-2 selective categories, with PA status and specific step-therapy criteria for each non-preferred formulation. MassHealth does not name one single 'preferred' NSAID brand/generic in this table (unlike the diabetes/cardiovascular tables) — naproxen tablet/capsule was selected as the representative preferred agent for this checkpoint's schema because it is one of the widely-covered, no-PA, generic-first-line oral NSAIDs alongside ibuprofen and celecoxib; this specific single-agent framing is an inference layered onto the verified underlying per-drug PA data. Mandatory/allowable 90-day supply (A90) applies broadly across covered formulations. Also mentions '90-day supply' policy and general brand-vs-generic preference statement.",
      "sourceIds": [
        "masshealth-nsaids-source-2026-07-07"
      ],
